						 <p>I liked it. I appreciated the absurdism, and I thought it was an entertaining read.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">I&nbsp;even&nbsp;imagined&nbsp;that&nbsp;final&nbsp;test...</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">I&nbsp;even&nbsp;imagined&nbsp;that&nbsp;final&nbsp;test.</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>Dr. Pollock strode rapidly into the room, separated by a pane of glass for observation of the Testing Chamber from today's subject.</p> <p>&quot;Sorry I'm late, what did I miss?&quot;</p> <p>&quot;We're already at the final phase almost,&quot; Dr. Codey hissed back.</p> <p>&quot;Fine, fine,&quot; grumbled Pollock. &quot;Just quickly bring me up to speed. Please.&quot;</p> <p>&quot;Subject consumed the item some minutes ago,&quot; Junior Researcher Leon recapped the notes. &quot;This one was another rarity, different orifice than the mouth that the paper appeared.&quot;</p> <p>&quot;Oh, from the ear? Or the nose? Disgusting; glad I wasn't here to see that then!&quot;</p> <p>&quot;Actually sir,&quot; Leon was grinning broadly and almost tittered out loud. &quot;It was-&quot;</p> <p>A sharp glare from Dr. Codey stopped him cold. Leon would have to be content with imagining the look on Pollock's face when he read that detail later on.</p> <p>&quot;Well, they're going to read the document now.&quot;</p> <p>Pollock stepped forward and keyed the mic to speak to the test subject in the adjacent room. &quot;D-4573, read out loud the paper now in your posession.&quot;</p> <p>Nervously, D-4573 began: &quot;Item number, zero bones. Object class, no bones. B—b-bone class,&nbsp;none. Bone class:&nbsp;none.&quot; Frantically they looked to the mirror reflection they knew the scientists were behind. &quot;Guys? Guys… what is this?&quot;</p> <p>Dr. Pollock leaned over the table to observe the SCP documentation as it currently stood; Dr. Codey dilligently pointed out the second paragraph of the Description.</p> <p>&quot;D-4573,&quot; Pollock monotoned into the mic, &quot;please finish reading.&quot;</p> <p>Dr. Codey hurried out soon after the conclusion of testing, citing an appointment with the Site's Chief of Containment for the bi-weekly protocol review. Dr. Pollock gathered up the necessary documents to complete the Test Summary.</p> <p>&quot;Leon,&quot; announced Pollock as he left the room himself, &quot;get in touch with the custodians. They'll handle the mess in there.&quot; Over his shoulder, he added:</p> <p>&quot;I don't know if they have such a thing handy on the Site here, but… You might suggest they bring a snow shovel.&quot;</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
